### Inverse Images

For $f:X\to Y$, we have a map on presheaves `
\begin{align*}  
f^{-1} :{\operatorname{Presh}}(Y_{\mathrm{\text{ét}}}) &\to {\operatorname{Presh}}(X_\mathrm{\text{ét}}) \\
\mathcal{F}(V\xrightarrow{\mathrm{\text{ét}}} X) &\mapsto \varinjlim\mathcal{F}(U\to X)
,\end{align*}`{=tex} where the limit is over diagrams of the form
```{=tex}
\begin{tikzcd}
V \ar[r] \ar[d, "\mathrm{\text{ét}}"] & U \ar[d, "\mathrm{\text{ét}}"] \\
X \ar[r] & Y
\end{tikzcd}
```
::: {.fact}
```{=latex}
\begin{fact}
```
$f^{-1}$ is left adjoint to pushforward as functors on presheaves.

```{=latex}
\end{fact}
```
