::: {.proposition title="Properties of étale cohomology"}
```{=latex}
\begin{proposition}[Properties of étale cohomology]
```
```{=tex}
\envlist
```
1.  $H^0(X_\mathrm{\text{ét}}, \mathcal{F}) = \mathcal{F}(X)$, aka the
    global sections $\Gamma(X, \mathcal{F})$.

2.  $H^{>0}(\mathcal{I}) = 0$ for $\mathcal{I}$ injective.

3.  Given a SES of sheaves in
    ${\operatorname{Sh}}(X_\mathrm{\text{ét}})$ `
    \begin{align*}  
    0 \to A\to B \to C \to 0
    \end{align*}`{=tex} there is a LES `
    \begin{align*}  
      \cdots \to H^{i+1}(X_\mathrm{\text{ét}}, C) \xrightarrow{\delta} H^i(X_\mathrm{\text{ét}}, A) \to \cdots
      .\end{align*}`{=tex}

```{=latex}
\end{proposition}
```
